template.description:
Area charts are used to show continuous data over time. Examples include stock prices, temperatures, indexes and rates.

The X axis (base axis) on a line chart always runs along a date range, for example, 1992 to 2012. 

Your data should include one column of dates. Check out the available date formats on the Axes tab, and format your dates in your spreadsheet according to one of these.

You should have one column of data for each line in your chart.
